         <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
            <ab>
               <lb n="1"/>To the sacred shades.
               <lb n="2"/>For Pompeia Augurina, daughter of Gnaeus, most pious mother, the children of Publius Aelius, Nigrinus and Augurina, made (this) <!--(and)--> for their freedmen and freedwomen and their descendants. <!-- I prefer "Aelius Nigrinus and Aelia Augurina, children of Publius" as discussed, because I think it's more literal, but there's not really much difference in meaning. Also, whose freedmen and -women and whose descendants? I had assumed it would be the freedmen and -women of Pompeia Augurina actually, and obviously the descendants would refer to those of the freedmen and -women (as eorum makes clear), but I suppose it could equally be the freedmen and -women of P. Aelius Nigrinus and Aelia Augurina.-->
            </ab>
